le?language=EN>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>I didn't like LOTR<BR>Blasphemer!!!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/02 1:14:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16591.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana Batteries</span><hr size=1> Theoretically any PoS quest item can be recharged. You buy the battery (and I forget which one to buy), and combine it in a toolbox (which they also sell there) to recharge.<br><br>I *think* it was type 3 batteries for 3-charge items, and type 5 batteries for 5-charge items. But I also *think* it's been nerfed or broken, too, and doesn't work any more.<br><br><br>They also sell the mana batteries at the pirates in Iceclad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufrozboz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frozboz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/02 1:16:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16591.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://frozboz.homestead.com/files/vulak-small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana Batteries</span><hr size=1> Yes, to recharge items.. specifically PoA quest items.  For instance, the Amulet of the Void.  Place the used amulet + class 5 mana battery into a box of the void, press combine, and you've recharged it.<br><br>Other uses for mana batteries include Gnomish tinkering devices, like the Gnomish Vanishing Device.  Place a mana battery + GVD inside a toolbox and combine. <p><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Tahoma" size="2"><a href=